I13(F) If the disbursements were paid out of funds not described in subparagraph (E), the names and addresses of all contributors who contributed an aggregate amount of $1,000 or more to the person making the disbursement during the period beginning on the first day of the preceding calendar year and ending on the disclosure date.

I79(3) Electioneering communication

I12For purposes of this subsection_

I18(A) In general

I13(i) The term ``electioneering communication'' means any broadcast, cable, or satellite communication which_

I14(I) refers to a clearly identified candidate for Federal office;

I14(II) is made within_

I16(aa) 60 days before a general, special, or runoff election for the office sought by the candidate; or

I16(bb) 30 days before a primary or preference election, or a convention or caucus of a political party that has authority to nominate a candidate, for the office sought by the candidate; and

Q04

I14(III) in the case of a communication which refers to a candidate for an office other than President or Vice President, is targeted to the relevant electorate.

Q04

I13(ii) If clause (i) is held to be constitutionally insufficient by final judicial decision to support the regulation provided herein, then the term ``electioneering communication'' means any broadcast, cable, or satellite communication which promotes or supports a candidate for that office, or attacks or opposes a candidate for that office (regardless of whether the communication expressly advocates a vote for or against a candidate) and which also is suggestive of no plausible meaning other than an exhortation to vote for or against a specific candidate. Nothing in this subparagraph shall be construed to affect the interpretation or application of section 100.22(b) of title 11, Code of Federal Regulations.

I18(B) Exceptions

I13The term ``electioneering communication'' does not include_

I14(i) a communication appearing in a news story, commentary, or editorial distributed through the facilities of any broadcasting station, unless such facilities are owned or controlled by any political party, political committee, or candidate;

I14(ii) a communication which constitutes an expenditure or an independent expenditure under this Act;

I14(iii) a communication which constitutes a candidate debate or forum conducted pursuant to regulations adopted by the Commission, or which solely promotes such a debate or forum and is made by or on behalf of the person sponsoring the debate or forum; or

I14(iv) any other communication exempted under such regulations as the Commission may promulgate (consistent with the requirements of this paragraph) to ensure the appropriate implementation of this paragraph, except that under any such regulation a communication may not be exempted if it meets the requirements of this paragraph and is described in section 431(20)(A)(iii) of this title.

I18(C) Targeting to relevant electorate

I13For purposes of this paragraph, a communication which refers to a clearly identified candidate for Federal office is ``targeted to the relevant electorate'' if the communication can be received by 50,000 or more persons_

I14(i) in the district the candidate seeks to represent, in the case of a candidate for Representative in, or Delegate or Resident Commissioner to, the Congress; or

I14(ii) in the State the candidate seeks to represent, in the case of a candidate for Senator.

I79(4) Disclosure date

I12For purposes of this subsection, the term ``disclosure date'' means_

I13(A) the first date during any calendar year by which a person has made disbursements for the direct costs of producing or airing electioneering communications aggregating in excess of $10,000; and

I13(B) any other date during such calendar year by which a person has made disbursements for the direct costs of producing or airing electioneering communications aggregating in excess of $10,000 since the most recent disclosure date for such calendar year.

I79(5) Contracts to disburse

I12For purposes of this subsection, a person shall be treated as having made a disbursement if the person has executed a contract to make the disbursement.

I79(6) Coordination with other requirements

I12Any requirement to report under this subsection shall be in addition to any other reporting requirement under this Act.

I79(7) Coordination with title 26

I12Nothing in this subsection may be construed to establish, modify, or otherwise affect the definition of political activities or electioneering activities (including the definition of participating in, intervening in, or influencing or attempting to influence a political campaign on behalf of or in opposition to any candidate for public office) for purposes of title 26.

