I16(III) the limits under subsection (d) of this section with respect to any expenditure by a State or national committee of a political party shall not apply.

I18(D) Opposition personal funds amount

I13The opposition personal funds amount is an amount equal to the excess (if any) of_

I14(i) the greatest aggregate amount of expenditures from personal funds (as defined in section 434(a)(6)(B) of this title) that an opposing candidate in the same election makes; over

I14(ii) the aggregate amount of expenditures from personal funds made by the candidate with respect to the election.

I18(E) Special rule for candidate's campaign funds

I77(i) In general

I14For purposes of determining the aggregate amount of expenditures from personal funds under subparagraph (D)(ii), such amount shall include the gross receipts advantage of the candidate's authorized committee.

