I12The Chief Administrative Officer shall_

I13(A) oversee all financial management activities relating to the programs and operations of the Capitol Police;

I13(B) develop and maintain an integrated accounting and financial system for the Capitol Police, including financial reporting and internal controls, which_

I14(i) complies with applicable accounting principles, standards, and requirements, and internal control standards;

I14(ii) complies with any other requirements applicable to such systems; and

I14(iii) provides for_

I16(I) complete, reliable, consistent, and timely information which is prepared on a uniform basis and which is responsive to financial information needs of the Capitol Police;

I16(II) the development and reporting of cost information;

I16(III) the integration of accounting and budgeting information; and

I16(IV) the systematic measurement of performance;

